{
  "description": "A close-up photograph features a tulip in partial bloom, bathed in dramatic lighting. The tulip is predominantly orange, transitioning to a warmer, reddish hue at the edges of its petals. The flower is viewed from a low angle, with the bud's tightly-closed petals forming a dynamic, almost architectural shape. Green sepals cradle the base of the flower. To the right, a blurred, deep-red flower is partially visible, suggesting a bouquet or grouping of blossoms. A vertical stem, also green, runs alongside the orange tulip, adding to the composition. The background is dark and indistinct, creating a strong contrast and focusing attention on the tulips. The lighting highlights the texture of the petals, creating a sense of depth and volume.",
